The paper presents a new static analysis technique for probabilistic programs that combines manual reasoning techniques with automatic resource-bound analysis. This involves the use of program logics and weakest preconditions, which are typically associated with programming languages and semantics (cs.PL). The analysis is also based on Markov decision processes, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and probabilistic modeling (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the soundness of the analysis, which is a topic often studied in logic (cs.LO) and software engineering (cs.SE).
